# CombatMode Architecture and Style

Use this project map and conventions for all changes.

## Runtime structure

- `CombatMode.toc`: addon metadata, `SavedVariables: CombatModeDB`, load order entrypoint.
- `Embeds.xml`: loads Lua files and owns the root frame scripts (`OnEvent`, `OnUpdate` bridge).
- `Features/*.lua`: runtime systems and gameplay behavior.
- `Config/*.lua`: AceConfig option builders and category assembly.
- `UI/CrosshairEditMode.lua`: Edit Mode integration for crosshair controls.
- `Bindings.xml`: keybinding declarations and binding click targets.

## Module responsibilities

- `Features/Core.lua`: addon lifecycle, global event/update orchestration, mouselook driver.
- `Features/Constants.lua`: defaults, static tables, event groups, paths.
- `Features/Reticle.lua`: reticle/crosshair behavior and action-targeting CVars.
- `Features/ClickCasting.lua`: click-cast override macros and modifiers.
- `Features/CursorUnlock.lua`: auto mouselook unlock logic (UI/Lua conditions).
- `Features/Pulse.lua`: post-unlock cursor pulse effect.
- `Features/HealingRadial.lua`: healing radial menu, targeting/casting flow.
- `Config/Config.lua`: assembles all option groups into Blizzard/Ace settings.
- `Config/*Options.lua`: feature-specific settings panels.

## Required coding conventions

- Keep event wiring centralized via constants and core dispatch; avoid ad-hoc event frames.
- Prefer extending existing `CM` feature APIs over introducing new global state.
- Respect combat lockdown and secure action patterns (`SecureActionButtonTemplate`, macro attributes).
- Use existing DB scopes consistently:
  - account-wide in `CM.DB.global`
  - character-specific in `CM.DB.char`
- Put new user-facing settings in `Config/*Options.lua` and wire through `Config/Config.lua`.
- Preserve slash command and keybinding behavior unless change is explicitly requested.

## Change expectations

- Follow current file header purpose comments as source of truth for module intent.
- Keep edits minimal and local to the owning module.
- Call out behavior changes that affect mouselook, targeting CVars, or binding overrides.
